      • LimitedSizeIntersectIteration

        public LimitedSizeIntersectIteration(Iteration<? extends BindingSet,? extends QueryEvaluationException> arg1,
                                     Iteration<? extends BindingSet,? extends QueryEvaluationException> arg2,
                                     AtomicLong used,
                                     long maxSize)
        Creates a new IntersectIteration that returns the intersection of the results of two Iterations. By default, duplicates are not filtered from the results.
        Parameters:
        arg1 - An Iteration containing the first set of elements.
        arg2 - An Iteration containing the second set of elements.
        used - An atomic long used to monitor how many elements are in the set collections.
        maxSize - Maximum size allowed by the sum of all collections used by the LimitedSizeQueryEvaluatlion.
